l test examples, and the tip about setters/getters with logic, plus the PostNo image.\n\n**s5**: Configuration items section looks comprehensive.\n\n**s6**: Component configuration example is correct.\n\nMoving into the V2 verification now, I'm looking at s2 and noticing the knowledge file references a cross-reference about group specification and message specification methods.\n\nChecking against the source, I can see the knowledge file accurately captures that both group and message specification methods follow the same approach documented in the charset and string length unit test section.\n\nLooking at the footnotes in the source, there's a note about how group specification is handled.\n\nNow examining the section structure in the RST source to understand the heading hierarchy and organization of the test case creation methods. Looking at the document structure, I can see the hierarchy uses `====` for h2-level sections and `----` for h3-level sections. The file appears to be a mid-document fragment showing test case documentation with nested sections on test methods, table creation, and component configuration examples. I see the issue now—in RST format, the first character used sets the hierarchy level, so `====` marks the top-level headings while `----` marks the second level. Looking at how the knowledge file sections map to these heading levels, I'm counting 6 distinct sections that align with the document structure, which matches what the V3 validation is checking for. I'm checking whether `EntityTestSupport` should be listed as a hint for s4 since it appears in the code as a parent class, though it's already documented in s1 and s3, so this cross-reference might be acceptable. For s1, I'm verifying that `testSingleValidation` and the single-item validation test concept are properly captured in the hints.\n\nNow looking at s2, I'm seeing that while `testShots`, `params`, and the `@AssertTrue` annotation are all documented, the example class names like `UserRegistrationFormTest`, `SystemUserEntity`, and `UserTelEntity` aren't appearing in the hints—these seem to be concrete implementation examples rather than core concepts that need to be extracted.\n\nFor s3, `testBeanValidation` and `EntityTestSupport` are covered, but again the `UserRegistrationForm` classes aren't in the hints since they're just illustrative examples.\n\nThe s5 section looks solid with all the configuration properties and strategy classes accounted for, and s6 has extensive class name coverage.\n\nLooking back at the source more carefully, I'm noticing the file begins with what appears to be Japanese text about test methods, so I should examine whether there's content being missed or if some items are being incorrectly identified as part of the API. Looking at the rest of the footnote for expectedMessageId, it explains that when multiple messages are expected, you add numbered suffixes like expectedMessageId2 and propertyName2 to extend the pattern. The source also includes a contextual note about the diagram showing how to create test cases for a property that validates whether two password fields match, which isn't captured in the knowledge file. Looking at how the knowledge file handles the setter/getter example - it seems to cut off mid-sentence when describing the logic. The source material shows a concrete test case with specific postal code values (upper 3 digits: 001, lower 4 digits: 0001) that should combine into a 7-digit postal code, but the knowledge file's supplementary note appears incomplete, trailing off without finishing the explanation of what the getter returns. セッターやゲッターにロジックが含まれている場合、そのロジックが正しく動作することを確認するテストケースが必要だ。ドキュメントには郵便番号の例が示されており、上3桁と下4桁に分かれたセッターから7桁の郵便番号を正しく取得するゲッターの動作を検証するテストが記載されている。また、ドキュメントの構成を見ると、項目間精査、セッター・ゲッターテスト、自動テストフレームワーク設定値といった主要なセクションがあり、各セクション内にテストメソッドの作成方法やテストケース表の作成といった詳細が含まれているようだ。\n\n知識ファイルの6つのセクションでこれらの内容がカバーされているか確認する必要があるが、各セクションが十分な内容を持っているようなので、大きな漏れはなさそうだ。\n\nsetter/getterテストの説明も適切に要約されており、実装例も含